# Multi-validators

This PR enables the ability to define a special kind of validator that let's you use the same script hash for **all four** script purposes.

## Syntax

```
/// no params
validator {
  fn foo(d, r, c) -> Bool {
    True
  }
  
  fn bar(r, c) -> Bool {
    True
  }
}

/// with params
validator(param: ByteArray) {
  fn foo(d, r, c) -> Bool {
    True
  }
  
  fn bar(r, c) -> Bool {
    True
  } 
}
```

In the parameterized example, `param` is available inside both `foo` and `bar`.

